  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And an odd thing happened as we went streaming south, we suddenly heard-- the radio started to chatter from CCR, Combat Command Reserve-- We got a bridge, we got a bridge, we got a bridge over the Danube.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Like, holy cow.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, intact, seizing it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was like the bridge they seized at the Rhine a couple months before.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in fact, they had.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Task Force [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Ippolito, ?] under a little Italian New York kid named Ippolito, went into the town with guns blazing and shot up everything, and the Germans dived in their hole.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They ran across the bridge, they got the demolitions, which were big airplane bombs wired to go up, and they cut the wires before they could explode them, and threw them in the Danube, and we had a bridge over the Danube.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, the odd thing was it got in the army histories.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then, the radio said, hey, the bridge is blown.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We looked, we are just a couple-- when a bridge goes up, you see it from a long way off.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We said, it didn't blow.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And all the confusion went back, the bridge over the Danube, went all the way to army headquarters, Seventh Army, everyone was-- the bridge-- they had a bridge, but it got blown, and it's all in the history books.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then it turned out, no it wasn't.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Ippolito ?] remembered what he heard that morning at the briefing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He said we've got a ridge over the river, and it's blue.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this was turned into blown.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyway, we pulled up in the-- for the night at the picture I've shown you, at the Castle Hochstadt, which is a 1,000-year-old castle that Napoleon had used for headquarters.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
